OutOfMemoryException indicates that the system does not have enough free memory to create an object or complete an operation.

This error is usually related to the application hitting its own allocated memory limits or the fragmentation of the managed heap,
rather than the computer running out of total RAM capacity.

List<string> leakList = new List<string>();

while(true)
{
    // A massive string is added in each iteration
    leakList.Add(new string('A', 1000000)); 
}
